'''睡眠不足'''（{{lang-en|Sleep deprivation}}，也稱為sleep insufficiency，或是sleeplessness），是指沒充足的[[睡眠|睡眠]]時間和/或睡眠品質來支持個人良好的警覺性、表現、和健康。這種症狀或是[[慢性病|慢性]]的，或是急性的，有各式不同的嚴重程度。
 
急性睡眠不足是指個人的睡眠時間比平時少，或在短時間內根本不睡覺 - 通常持續的時間是一到兩天。慢性（長期）睡眠不足是指個人長期睡眠時間低於理想的時間長度。長期睡眠不足經常與[[失眠|失眠]]混淆。雖然長期睡眠不足和失眠都是睡眠時間長度和/或品質降低，而且是身體功能受損，但其間的區別在於入睡的能力。睡眠不足的人在正常的情況下能快速入睡，但失眠的人是難以入眠。<ref>{{Cite book|title=International Classification of Sleep Disorders|publisher=American Academy of Sleep Medicine|year=2014|edition=3|location=Darien, IL}}</ref>
 
長期讓睡眠時間受限會對[[大腦|大腦]]和{{le|睡眠不足對認知能力的影響|Effects of sleep deprivation on cognitive performance|認知功能}}產生不利影響。<ref name="Alhola">{{Cite journal |last=Alhola |first=Paula |author2=Päivi Polo-Kantola  |date=October 2007 |title=Sleep deprivation: Impact on cognitive performance |journal=Neuropsychiatr. Dis. Treat. |volume=3 |issue=5 |pages=553–567|quote=Although both conditions [total and partial SD] induce several negative effects including impairments in cognitive performance, the underlying mechanisms seem to be somewhat different. |pmc=2656292 |pmid=19300585}}</ref>然而在某些情況下，睡眠不足反而會讓精力和警覺性增加，以及改善情緒；睡眠不足甚至被用作治療[[抑鬱|抑鬱]]症的方法，但其長期後果尚未被評估過。<ref name="REM deprivation in healthy people">{{cite journal |vauthors=Nykamp K, Rosenthal L, Folkerts M, Roehrs T, Guido P, Roth, T |title=The effects of REM sleep deprivation on the level of sleepiness/alertness |journal=Sleep |volume=21 |issue=6 |pages=609–614 |date=September 1998 |pmid=9779520 |doi=10.1093/sleep/21.6.609 |doi-access=free }}</ref><ref name="Sleep and depression review">{{cite journal |vauthors=Riemann D, Berger M, Voderholzer U |title=Sleep and depression - results from psychobiological studies: an overview |journal=Biological Psychology |volume=57 |issue=1–3 |pages=67–103 |date=July–August 2001 |pmid=11454435 |doi=10.1016/s0301-0511(01)00090-4|s2cid=31725861 }}</ref>
 
對於急性的完全剝奪睡眠和長期的部分睡眠限制，其間影響的比較，少有人做過研究。<ref name="Alhola"/>人類長期不睡眠的情況並不常見（除非他們患有[[致死性家族失眠症|致命性失眠症]]，或是因為手術而引起的特定問題）；而短暫的[[微睡眠|微睡眠]]似乎也無法避免。<ref>{{cite book |title=Sleep deprivation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EaGWMXsR5XYC&pg=PA183 |last=Kushida |publisher=Informa Health Care |year=2005 |pages=1–2 |isbn=978-0-8247-5949-0 |access-date=2021-11-01 |archive-date=2021-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211042707/https://books.google.com/books?id=EaGWMXsR5XYC&pg=PA183 |dead-url=no }}</ref>長期完全把睡眠剝奪會導致受實驗動物的死亡。<ref>{{Cite journal |vauthors=Rechtschaffen A, Bergmann B|doi=10.1016/0166-4328(95)00020-T |title=Sleep deprivation in the rat by the disk-over-water method |year=1995 |journal=Behavioural Brain Research |volume=69 |pages=55–63 |pmid=7546318 |issue=1–2 |s2cid=4042505 }}</ref>

==原因==
===失眠===
{{main|失眠}}
 
失眠是六種睡眠異常症狀之一，有21–37%的成年人受其影響。<ref name="UKInsomnia">{{cite journal|last1=Morphy|first1=Hannah|last2=Dunn|first2=Kate M.|last3=Lewis|first3=Martyn|last4=Boardman|first4=Helen F.|last5=Croft|first5=Peter R.|date=2007|title=Epidemiology of Insomnia: a Longitudinal Study in a UK Population|url=http://www.journalsleep.org/ViewAbstract.aspx?pid=26762|url-status=live|journal=Sleep|volume=30|issue=3|pages=274–80|pmid=17425223|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222082309/http://www.journalsleep.org/ViewAbstract.aspx?pid=26762|archive-date=2015-12-22|access-date=2015-12-13}}</ref><ref name="JapanInsomnia">{{cite journal|last1=Kim|first1=K|last2=Uchiyama|first2=M|last3=Okawa|first3=M|last4=Liu|first4=X|last5=Ogihara|first5=R|date=2000-02-01|title=An epidemiological study of insomnia among the Japanese general population.|journal=Sleep|volume=23|issue=1|pages=41–7|doi=10.1093/sleep/23.1.1a|pmid=10678464|doi-access=free}}</ref>失眠有許多症狀很易識別，包括{{le|白天過度嗜睡|Excessive daytime sleepiness}}、[[挫折|沮喪]]或擔心睡眠、注意力/專注力/或記憶力方面的問題、極端[[心境|情緒]]變化或煩躁、缺乏精力或[[動機|動機]]、在學校或工作中表現不佳、以及緊張性的頭痛或是胃痛。
 
失眠可分為原發性和繼發性，或[[共病症|共病]]失眠。<ref name="WHO">{{cite web|title=Dyssomnias|url=https://www.who.int/selection_medicines/committees/expert/17/application/Section24_GAD.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318104517/http://www.who.int/selection_medicines/committees/expert/17/application/Section24_GAD.pdf|archive-date=2009-03-18|access-date=2009-01-25|publisher=WHO|pages=7–11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Buysse|first=Daniel J.|year=2008|title=Chronic Insomnia|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-psychiatry_2008-06_165_6/page/678|journal=Am. J. Psychiatry|volume=165|issue=6|pages=678–86|doi=10.1176/appi.ajp.2008.08010129|pmc=2859710|pmid=18519533|quote=For this reason, the NIH conference [of 2005] commended the term "comorbid insomnia" as a preferable alternative to the term "secondary insomnia."}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Erman|first=Milton K.|year=2007|title=Insomnia: Comorbidities and Consequences|url=http://www.primarypsychiatry.com/aspx/articledetail.aspx?articleid=1102|url-status=live|journal=Primary Psychiatry|volume=14|issue=6|pages=31–35|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715113025/http://www.primarypsychiatry.com/aspx/articledetail.aspx?articleid=1102|archive-date=2011-07-15|quote=Two general categories of insomnia exist, primary insomnia and comorbid insomnia.}}</ref>
 
原發性失眠是種[[睡眠障礙|睡眠障礙]]，無法歸因於醫學、精神、或環境的原因。<ref>{{cite web|author=World Health Organization|year=2007|title=Quantifying burden of disease from environmental noise|url=http://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/87638/Noise_EDB_2nd_mtg.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101123213411/http://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/87638/Noise_EDB_2nd_mtg.pdf|archive-date=2010-11-23|access-date=2010-09-22|page=20}}</ref>原發性失眠可分為三種主要類型: [[心理生理學|心理生理]]性失眠、[[原因不明|原因不明]]失眠、和{{le|睡眠狀態誤解|sleep state misperception}}(矛盾式失眠)。<ref name="WHO" />心理生理性失眠係由焦慮所引起。原因不明失眠通常始於童年，而會持續一生。有人認為這種失眠是大腦中控制睡眠 - 覺醒週期部分的神經化學問題，導致睡眠信號不足，或覺醒信號過度活躍的結果。當人們獲得足夠的睡眠，卻錯誤地認為他們的睡眠不足時，就會對自己的睡眠狀態有誤解。<ref>{{cite journal|vauthors=Chunhua L, Hongzhong Q|date=2017-06-15|title=Paradoxical Insomnia: Misperception of Sleep Can Be a Tormenting Experience|url=https://www.aafp.org/afp/2017/0615/p770.html|journal=American Family Physician|volume=95|issue=12|page=770|pmid=28671423|access-date=2020-05-10|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028041831/https://www.aafp.org/afp/2017/0615/p770.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}
 
繼發性失眠或共病失眠症與其他醫學、神經學、心理、和精神疾病同時發生。並不一定含有因果關係。<ref>Biological Rhythms, Sleep and Hypnosis by Simon Green</ref>
 
睡眠屬於累積性。表示個人因沒入睡（例如徹夜未眠），疲勞將會延續到第二天。幾天沒有獲得足夠的睡眠，累積起來就會形成不足現象，然後就是睡眠不足的所有症狀會出現。一個休息良好，且健康的人通常會在[[快速動眼期|快速動眼期]]（REM）睡眠階段花費較少時間。研究顯示，在快速眼動期睡眠階段所花費的時間與隨後清醒時期的時間呈反比關係。<ref>{{Cite book|author=Plaford, Gary R.|title=Sleep and learning : the magic that makes us healthy and smart|year=2009|isbn=9781607090915|location=Lanham|oclc=310224798}}</ref>
 
致命性失眠症是種[[神經退化障礙|神經退化障礙]]的病症，最終導致完全無法度過[[非快速動眼睡眠|非快速動眼睡眠]](NREM) 的第1階段。除失眠之外，患者可能會出現驚恐發作、[[偏執狂|偏執]]、恐懼症、[[幻覺|幻覺]]、體重快速下降、和[[失智症|失智症]]。患者通常在發病後7至36個月之間死亡。
 
===睡眠呼吸中止症===
{{main|睡眠呼吸中止症}}
 
阻塞性睡眠呼吸中止症通常是由上呼吸道在睡眠期間塌陷而導致流向肺部的空氣減少。患有這種症狀的人可能會因用力呼吸或是感到窒息而驚醒、睡眠不安、早晨頭痛、早晨意識模糊、或是[[易怒|易怒]]、和煩躁等症狀。有1%到10%的[[美國|美國]]人受到這種疾患的影響。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Zammit, Gary K.|url=https://archive.org/details/goodnightshowtos00zamm|title=Good nights : how to stop sleep deprivation, overcome insomnia, and get the sleep you need|date=1997|publisher=Andrews and McMeel|others=Zanca, Jane A.|isbn=0-8362-2188-5|location=Kansas City|oclc=35849087|url-access=registration}}</ref>如果不予治療，會產生許多嚴重的健康後果。使用[[持續正壓呼吸器|持續正壓呼吸器]]（CPAP）、APAP（Automatic positive airway pressure）、或是BPAP（Bilevel, or variable positive airway pressure）等器械給予氣道正壓的治療，都是針對這種症狀的一線治療選擇。<ref>Spicuzza L, Caruso D, Di Maria G. Obstructive sleep apnoea syndrome and its management. Therapeutic Advances in Chronic Disease. 2015;6(5):273-285. doi:10.1177/2040622315590318.</ref>在某些情況下，可使用下頜移位裝置，重新把下頜和舌頭定位，防止氣道塌陷。對於某些患者，可能要用到補充氧氣治療。如[[鼻中隔|鼻中隔]]偏曲等問題會關閉氣道，並增加[[粘膜|粘膜]]和[[鼻甲|鼻甲]]的腫脹，在某些情況下，採用矯正手術（{{le|鼻中隔成形術|septoplasty}}）會是合適的做法。
 
中樞性睡眠呼吸中止症是由於[[中樞神經系統|中樞神經系統]]未能在睡眠期間向身體發出呼吸信號所引起。可使用類似於阻塞性睡眠呼吸中止的治療法，以及其他治療方法（例如順應性支持換氣法（Adaptive Servo Ventilation）和某些藥物治療）。有些藥物（如鴉片類藥物）可能會引起或是造成中樞性睡眠呼吸中止。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Muza RT|year=2015|title=Central sleep apnoea—a clinical review|journal=Journal of Thoracic Disease|volume=7|issue=5|pages=930–937|doi=10.3978/j.issn.2072-1439.2015.04.45|pmc=4454847|pmid=26101651}}</ref>
 
===自願性睡眠剝奪===
由於缺乏睡眠慾望，或習慣性使用[[興奮劑|興奮劑]]，睡眠不足有時可能是自我強加所造成。睡眠剝奪也是為[[電影特技|特別]]表演中要打破[[世界紀錄|世界紀錄]]，以取得個人名望而自我強加的結果。
 
===精神病===
目前，世界有近四分之一的人口受到睡眠障礙的困擾。常年有睡眠問題的人更容易罹患[[精神疾患|精神疾患]]，如[[躁鬱症|躁鬱症]]、[[廣泛性焦慮症|廣泛性焦慮症]]、{{le|自殺念頭|suicidal ideation}}，尤其是抑鬱症。<ref>{{cite journal|last1= Fang|first1= Hong|last2= Sheng Tu|first2= Sheng|date= 2019-02-07|title= Depression in sleep disturbance: A review on a bidirectional relationship, mechanisms and treatment|url= https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/jcmm.14170|journal= Journal of Cellular and Molecular Medicine|volume= |issue= |pages= |doi= |access-date= 2021-10-02|archive-date= 2021-12-09|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211209093607/https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/jcmm.14170|dead-url= no}}</ref>。燥鬱症患者轉變為[[躁狂|躁狂]]之前通常會出現失眠期，<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=McKenna BS, Eyler LT | title = Overlapping prefrontal systems involved in cognitive and emotional processing in euthymic bipolar disorder and following sleep deprivation: a review of functional neuroimaging studies |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_clinical-psychology-review_2012-11_32_7/page/650 | journal = Clin Psychol Rev | volume = 32 | issue = 7 | pages = 650–663 | date = November 2012 | pmid = 22926687 | pmc = 3922056 | doi = 10.1016/j.cpr.2012.07.003 }}</ref>而且資料顯示在大約30%的患者中，會因睡眠不足而誘發躁狂狀態。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Young|first1=JW|last2=Dulcis|first2=D|title=Investigating the mechanism(s) underlying switching between states in bipolar disorder|journal=European Journal of Pharmacology|date=2015-07-15|volume=759|pages=151–62|doi=10.1016/j.ejphar.2015.03.019|pmid=25814263|pmc=4437855|url=http://www.escholarship.org/uc/item/05z312jn|access-date=2021-11-01|archive-date=2020-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809201815/https://escholarship.org/uc/item/05z312jn|dead-url=no}}</ref>睡眠不足會是最終導致躁狂症發生的共同途徑，<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Wehr|first1=TA|date=1987|title=Sleep reduction as a final common pathway in the genesis of mania|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-psychiatry_1987-02_144_2/page/201|journal=Am. J. Psychiatry|volume=144|issue=2|pages=201–204|doi=10.1176/ajp.144.2.201|pmid=3812788}}</ref>躁狂症患者通常對睡眠的需求會持續減少。<ref>{{cite book|author=American Psychiatry Association|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders|date=2013|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing |location=Arlington |isbn=978-0-89042-555-8 |pages=123–154 |edition=5th}}</ref>
 
睡眠不足的症狀和[[思覺失調症|精神分裂症]]的症狀平行發展，包括正性[[症狀|症狀]]（positive symptoms）和認知症狀。<ref name="Pocivavsek">{{cite journal|last1=Pocivavsek|first1=A|last2=Rowland|first2=LM|date=2018-01-13|title=Basic Neuroscience Illuminates Causal Relationship Between Sleep and Memory: Translating to Schizophrenia.|journal=Schizophrenia Bulletin|volume=44|issue=1|pages=7–14|doi=10.1093/schbul/sbx151|pmc=5768044|pmid=29136236}}</ref>
 
===學校===
{{see also|{{le|高等教育中睡眠不足問題|Sleep deprivation in higher education}}}}
 
美國[[非營利組織|非營利組織]]{{le|國家睡眠基金會|National Sleep Foundation}}引用一篇1996 年的論文，顯示大學院校學生每晚的平均睡眠時間少於6小時。<ref>{{Cite web|title=National Sleep Foundation Key Messages/Talking Points|url=https://sleepfoundation.org/sites/default/files/Drowsy%20Driving-Key%20Messages%20and%20Talking%20Points.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160418142432/https://sleepfoundation.org/sites/default/files/Drowsy%20Driving-Key%20Messages%20and%20Talking%20Points.pdf|archive-date=2016-04-18|access-date=2016-04-18}}</ref>在2018年所做的一項研究，強調學生需要睡個好覺，資料顯示在期末考當週的五個晚上平均睡8小時的學生在考試的得分高於那些沒睡足的學生。<ref>{{Cite web|last=Schroeder|first=Jackson|date=2018-12-07|title=Students Who Sleep 8 Hours Score Higher On Final Exams|url=https://www.tun.com/blog/students-who-sleep-8-hours-score-higher-on-final-exams/|access-date=2018-12-10|website=The University Network|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211044043/https://www.tun.com/blog/students-who-sleep-8-hours-score-higher-on-final-exams/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
在這項研究，有70.6%的學生報告睡眠時間少於8小時，有多達27%的學生面臨至少一種睡眠障礙的風險。<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Shelley D Hershner|author2=Ronald D Chervin|date=2014-06-23|title=Causes and consequences of sleepiness among college students|journal=Nature and Science of Sleep|volume=6|pages=73–84|doi=10.2147/NSS.S62907|pmc=4075951|pmid=25018659}}</ref>睡眠不足在一年級大學生中很常見，因為他們正處於適應大學生活和社交活動的壓力之中。
 
台灣[[國立中正大學|國立中正大學]]心理學系進行的一項研究，結論是大一新生每週的睡眠時間最少。<ref name="Sleep patterns in college students; Gender and grade differences">{{cite journal|author=Tsai LL, Li SP|last2=Li|year=2004|title=Sleep patterns in college students; Gender and grade differences|url=http://www.websciences.org/cftemplate/NAPS/archives/indiv.cfm?ID=20041266|url-status=live|journal=J. Psychosom. Res.|volume=56|issue=2|pages=231–7|doi=10.1016/S0022-3999(03)00507-5|pmid=15016583|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081220062545/http://www.websciences.org/cftemplate/NAPS/archives/indiv.cfm?ID=20041266|archive-date=2008-12-20}}</ref>
 
廣泛的使用不同方法論，對平日較晚開始上課的學校所做的研究，均報告對青少年的睡眠、健康、和學習有益處。相較之下，沒有研究顯示平日較早開始上課對學生的睡眠、健康、或學習有任何積極影響。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kelley|first1=Paul|last2=Lockley|first2=Steven|last3=Foster|first3=Russel|last4=Kelley|first4=Jonathan|date=2014-08-01|title=Synchronizing education to adolescent biology: 'let teens sleep, start school later'|journal=Learning, Media and Technology|volume=40|issue=2|page=220|doi=10.1080/17439884.2014.942666|doi-access=free}}</ref>在國際研究中得到的龐大的數據顯示，絕大多數教育機構的開始上課時間與青少年生理時鐘“同步”的開始上課時間相比，都過早。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kelley|first1=P.|last2=Lockley|first2=S. W.|date=2013-04-27|title=Synchronizing Education to Healthy Adolescent Brain Development: Sleep and Circadian Rhythms}}</ref>[[明尼蘇達大學|明尼蘇達大學]]在1997年所做的研究，把早上7點15分開始上學的學生與8點40分才開始上學的學生進行比較。研究發現在早上8點40分開始的學生有較多的睡眠，比較早上課的學生成績更好。<ref name="SleepDepReport" />有四分之一的美國高中生承認他們每週至少在課堂上睡著過一次。<ref name="SleepDepAbcNews">{{cite news|author=Randolph E. Schmid|date=2006-03-28|title=Sleep-deprived teens dozing off at school|work=ABC News|agency=Associated Press|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory?id=1775003|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208094359/https://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory?id=1775003|archive-date=2006-12-08}}</ref>
 
人類在少年時期，[[晝夜節律|晝夜節律]]和睡眠模式通常會發生顯著變化。對[[腦電圖|腦電圖]](EEG)的研究顯示，在青春期非快速動眼睡眠（NREM）期間，深度（第3階段）睡眠減少50%，[[delta波|delta波]]峰值幅度減少75%。學校的開始上課時間通常與相應的睡眠偏移延遲不相容，導致大多數青少年的睡眠時間不足。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Giedd JN|date=October 2009|title=Linking adolescent sleep, brain maturation, and behavior|journal=[[Journal_of_Adolescent_Health|Journal of Adolescent Health]]|volume=45|issue=4|pages=319–320|doi=10.1016/j.jadohealth.2009.07.007|pmc=3018343|pmid=19766933}}</ref>
 
===住院時的睡眠===
在[[荷蘭|荷蘭]]全國所做的研究發現，住在醫院的普通病房患者的睡眠與在家的相比，總睡眠時間較短（少83分鐘）、在夜間會醒來較多次，和早上較早醒來。超過70%的人因外部原因而醒來，例如被醫院工作人員喚醒(35.8%)。另外干擾睡眠的因素也包括其他患者的噪音、醫療器械、疼痛、和如廁。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Wesselius|first1=Hilde M.|last2=van den Ende|first2=Eva S.|last3=Alsma|first3=Jelmer|last4=ter Maaten|first4=Jan C.|last5=Schuit|first5=Stephanie C. E.|last6=Stassen|first6=Patricia M.|last7=de Vries|first7=Oscar J.|last8=Kaasjager|first8=Karin H. A. H.|last9=Haak|first9=Harm R.|last10=van Doormaal|first10=Frederiek F.|last11=Hoogerwerf|first11=Jacobien J.|date=2018-09-01|title=Quality and Quantity of Sleep and Factors Associated With Sleep Disturbance in Hospitalized Patients|journal=JAMA Internal Medicine|volume=178|issue=9|pages=1201–1208|doi=10.1001/jamainternmed.2018.2669|issn=2168-6106|pmc=6142965|pmid=30014139}}</ref>患者在[[加護病房|加護病房]]（ICU）的睡眠剝奪更為嚴重，由於自然發生的夜間分泌[[褪黑素|褪黑激素]]的峰值不存在，而可能把正常的睡眠 - 覺醒週期打亂。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Shilo|first1=L.|last2=Dagan|first2=Y.|last3=Smorjik|first3=Y.|last4=Weinberg|first4=U.|last5=Dolev|first5=S.|last6=Komptel|first6=B.|last7=Balaum|first7=H.|last8=Shenkman|first8=L.|date=May 1999|title=Patients in the Intensive Care Unit Suffer from Severe Lack of Sleep Associated with Loss of Normal Melatonin Secretion Pattern|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-the-medical-sciences_1999-05_317_5/page/278|journal=The American Journal of the Medical Sciences|volume=317|issue=5|pages=278–281|doi=10.1016/s0002-9629(15)40528-2|issn=0002-9629|pmid=10334113}}</ref>然而，由於住院患者的個人特質和臨床情況相當多樣，改善睡眠和晝夜節律的可能解決方案應根據個人情況，並在病房的可能範圍內量身定製。可考慮採取多種干預措施來幫助配合患者特質、改善醫院作業程序或是醫院環境。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Tan|first1=Xiao|last2=van Egmond|first2=Lieve|last3=Partinen|first3=Markku|last4=Lange|first4=Tanja|last5=Benedict|first5=Christian|date=2019-07-01|title=A narrative review of interventions for improving sleep and reducing circadian disruption in medical inpatients|journal=Sleep Medicine|volume=59|pages=42–50|doi=10.1016/j.sleep.2018.08.007|issn=1389-9457|pmid=30415906|doi-access=free}}</ref>
 
===互聯網===
一項刊載在《{{le|經濟行為與組織雜誌|Journal of Economic Behavior and Organisation }}》上的研究報告說使用寬頻互聯網與睡眠不足有關聯。研究的結論是，有寬頻服務的人比沒有的人往往會少睡25分鐘，因此他們不太可能達到有科學根據的7-9小時睡眠。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Broadband internet causes sleep deprivation, a new study finds|work=ScienceDaily|url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2018/08/180802102340.htm|access-date=2018-08-10|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211042821/https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2018/08/180802102340.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>另一項對[[沙烏地紹德國王大學|沙烏地紹德國王大學]]附屬{{le|醫學城|King Saud Medical City}}435名非醫務人員進行的研究顯示，十分之九的受訪者在就寢時間會使用[[智慧型手機|智慧型手機]]，最常用的是[[社群媒體|社群媒體]](80.5%)。研究發現，睡前使用智慧型手機超過60分鐘的參與者比使用時間少於15分鐘的參與者，有高於7.4倍的機會會有較差的睡眠品質。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Alshobaili |first1=Fahdah |last2=AlYousefi |first2=Nada |title=The effect of smartphone usage at bedtime on sleep quality among Saudi non- medical staff at King Saud University Medical City |journal=J Family Med Prim Care |date=2019-06-26 |volume=8 |issue=6 |pages=1953–1957 |doi=10.4103/jfmpc.jfmpc_269_19 |pmid=31334161 |url=https://www.jfmpc.com/article.asp?issn=2249-4863;year=2019;volume=8;issue=6;spage=1953;epage=1957;aulast=Alshobaili |access-date=2021-08-18 |pmc=6618184 |archive-date=2020-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126083513/https://www.jfmpc.com/article.asp?issn=2249-4863;year=2019;volume=8;issue=6;spage=1953;epage=1957;aulast=Alshobaili |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
==影響和後果==
