===注意力和工作記憶===
睡眠不足會導致的身體後果中，最重要的應該是造成注意力和[[工作記憶|工作記憶]]的缺陷；<ref name="Alhola" />這種在日常生活中的失誤會導致不良的結果，從烹飪時時忘記添加配料，到做筆記時漏記一句。做事所需的注意力似乎與每晚的睡眠時數相關聯，注意力會隨著睡眠時數減少而下降。<ref>{{Cite book|title = An Introduction to Brain and Behavior|url = https://archive.org/details/introductiontobr0000kolb|last1 = Kolb|first1 = Bryan|publisher = Worth Publishers|year = 2014|isbn = 9781429242288|location = New York, New York|pages = 468–469|last2 = Whishaw|first2 = Ian|edition = 4th}}</ref>工作記憶可透過[[心理測時法|心理測時法]]等方法做測試。<ref name="Alhola" />
 
注意力失誤也會擴展到更為關鍵的領域，後果可能會攸關生死。因睡眠不足導致的注意力不集中會導致車禍和工業災難。研究人員為測量注意力缺陷程度，通常採用{{le|精神運動警戒測試法|psychomotor vigilance task}}(PVT)，這項測試要求受試者在隨機時間間隔燈光閃亮時按下按鈕。未能因應刺激（光）而按下按鈕，被當作發生錯誤，錯誤發生的原因是來自睡眠剝奪之後所引發的[[微睡眠|微睡眠]]。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Innes|first1=Carrie R. H.|last2=Poudel|first2=Govinda R.|last3=Jones|first3=Richard D.|date=2013-11-01|title=Efficient and Regular Patterns of Nighttime Sleep are Related to Increased Vulnerability to Microsleeps Following a Single Night of Sleep Restriction|url=https://doi.org/10.3109/07420528.2013.810222|journal=Chronobiology International|volume=30|issue=9|pages=1187–1196|doi=10.3109/07420528.2013.810222|pmid=23998288|s2cid=4682794|issn=0742-0528}}</ref>
 
重要的是，個人對其疲勞的主觀評估通常無法預測PVT的實際表現。雖然完全睡眠不足的人通常會知道到他們受到損害的程度，但慢性（較輕）睡眠剝奪所產生的失誤會隨著時間的推移而累積，因此他們的數量和嚴重程度與完全（急性）睡眠剝奪造成的結果相同。然而，長期睡眠不足的人會認為自己的受損程度遠低於完全睡眠不足的參與者。<ref name="SleepDepPVT">{{cite journal |vauthors=Van Dongen HA |title=The cumulative cost of additional wakefulness: dose-response effects on neurobehavioral functions and sleep physiology from chronic sleep restriction and total sleep deprivation |journal=Sleep |volume=26 |issue=2 |pages=117–26 |year=2002 |url=http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/DrowsyDriving.pdf |pmid=12683469  |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718152642/http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/DrowsyDriving.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-18  |doi=10.1093/sleep/26.2.117 |doi-access=free }}</ref>由於人們在評估自己執行任務（如駕車等）的能力時通常會採取主觀的態度，這樣的評估可能會導致他們得出錯誤的結論，而在需要持續注意的時候，但實際上他們的能力已經受到損害。
 
===情緒===
睡眠不足會對情緒產生負面影響。熬夜或突然上夜班會使人感到煩躁。等睡上一覺之後，情緒往往會恢復到基線或是正常。即使是部分的睡眠剝奪也會對情緒產生重大影響。在一項研究中，受試者報告說會增加嗜睡、疲勞、情緒混亂、緊張、和總體情緒障礙的程度，而這些都在一到兩個晚上的充分睡眠後恢復到基線水準。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Sleep and Mood {{!}} Need Sleep|url=http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu/need-sleep/whats-in-it-for-you/mood#1.|access-date=2021-01-21|website=healthysleep.med.harvard.edu|archive-date=2021-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210321052445/http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu/need-sleep/whats-in-it-for-you/mood#1.|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Dinges|first1=D. F.|last2=Pack|first2=F.|last3=Williams|first3=K.|last4=Gillen|first4=K. A.|last5=Powell|first5=J. W.|last6=Ott|first6=G. E.|last7=Aptowicz|first7=C.|last8=Pack|first8=A. I. Date=April 1997|title=Cumulative sleepiness, mood disturbance, and psychomotor vigilance performance decrements during a week of sleep restricted to 4-5 hours per night|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9231952|journal=Sleep|year=1997|volume=20|issue=4|pages=267–277|issn=0161-8105|pmid=9231952|access-date=2021-11-01|archive-date=2021-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211227120749/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9231952/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
[[抑鬱|抑鬱]]和睡眠是雙向關係。睡眠不足會導致抑鬱症的發展，抑鬱症會導致失眠、[[嗜睡症|嗜睡症]]、或[[阻塞型睡眠呼吸暫停|阻塞型睡眠呼吸暫停]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Depression and Sleep|url=https://www.sleepfoundation.org/mental-health/depression-and-sleep|access-date=2021-01-21|website=Sleep Foundation|language=en|archive-date=2021-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222005347/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/mental-health/depression-and-sleep|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Franzen|first1=Peter L.|last2=Buysse|first2=Daniel J.|date=2008|title=Sleep disturbances and depression: risk relationships for subsequent depression and therapeutic implications|journal=Dialogues in Clinical Neuroscience|volume=10|issue=4|pages=473–481|doi=10.31887/DCNS.2008.10.4/plfranzen|issn=1294-8322|pmc=3108260|pmid=19170404}}</ref>在成年抑鬱症患者中，約有75%會出現失眠。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Nutt|first1=David|last2=Wilson|first2=Sue|last3=Paterson|first3=Louise|date=2008|title=Sleep disorders as core symptoms of depression|journal=Dialogues in Clinical Neuroscience |volume=10|issue=3|pages=329–336|doi=10.31887/DCNS.2008.10.3/dnutt|issn=1294-8322|pmc=3181883|pmid=18979946}}</ref>睡眠不足，無論程度如何，都會引起嚴重的焦慮，而更增時間的睡眠不足，往往會導致焦慮水準的增加。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Pires|first1=Gabriel Natan|last2=Bezerra|first2=Andreia Gomes|last3=Tufik|first3=Sergio|last4=Andersen|first4=Monica Levy|date=August 2016|title=Effects of acute sleep deprivation on state anxiety levels: a systematic review and meta-analysis|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27810176|journal=Sleep Medicine|volume=24|pages=109–118|doi=10.1016/j.sleep.2016.07.019|issn=1878-5506|pmid=27810176|access-date=2021-11-01|archive-date=2021-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211102124104/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27810176/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
睡眠不足也會對情緒有些積極的影響，並可用於治療抑鬱症。<ref name="Sleep and depression review" />個人{{le|生物時鐘|Chronotype}}在睡眠不足時，會影響情緒的作用。那些在早上精神較好的人（早睡型，或稱“{{le|早鳥型|Lark (person)}}”）在睡眠剝奪後會變得更加沮喪，而那些在晚上精神較好的人（遲睡型，或稱“[[夜貓子|夜貓子]]”）反會顯現出情緒改善。<ref>{{cite journal|last=Selvi|first=Yavuz|author2=Mustafa Gulec|author3=Mehmet Yucel Agargun|author4=Lutfullah Besiroglu|year=2007|title=Mood changes after sleep deprivation in morningness–eveningness chronotypes in healthy individuals|url=http://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/85192141/2006-selvi.pdf|url-status=live|journal=Journal of Sleep Research|volume=16|issue=3|pages=241–4|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2869.2007.00596.x|pmid=17716271|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141215025258/https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/85192141/2006-selvi.pdf|archive-date=2014-12-15|s2cid=42338269|doi-access=free}}</ref>
 
情緒和精神狀態也會影響睡眠。焦慮或壓力讓躁動和覺醒增加，會讓個人更加覺醒、清醒、和警覺。<ref name=":0" />
 
===駕車能力===
{{main|{{le|睡眠不足狀態下駕車|Sleep-deprived driving}}}}
 
睡眠不足的危險更會在道路上凸顯；{{le|美國睡眠醫學會|American Academy of Sleep Medicine}}(AASM)報告說，有五分之一的嚴重機動車傷害與駕駛員疲勞有關，每天有80,000名車輛駕駛在駕駛時睡著，每年有250,000起[[交通事故|交通事故]]與睡眠有關聯，<ref name="DrowsyDriving">{{cite web |title=Drowsy Driving Fact Sheet |url=http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/DrowsyDriving.pdf |work=American Academy of Sleep Medicine |date=2009-12-02 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718152642/http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/DrowsyDriving.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-18  }}</ref>但[[美國國家公路交通安全管理局|美國國家公路交通安全管理局]]認為交通事故的數字只接近100,000起。<ref name="SleepDepReport">{{cite journal|author=Carpenter|first=Siri|author-link=Siri Carpenter|year=2001|title=Sleep deprivation may be undermining teen health|url=http://www.apa.org/monitor/oct01/sleepteen.html|url-status=live|journal=Monitor on Psychology|volume=32|issue=9|page=42|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061006064800/http://www.apa.org/monitor/oct01/sleepteen.html|archive-date=2006-10-06}}</ref>AASM建議駕駛在感覺困倦時，把車輛駛離公路，並{{le|小睡|nap}}15或20分鐘後再重新上路。<ref name="DrowsyDriving" />
 
根據2000年發表在[[英國醫學期刊|英國醫學期刊]]上的一項研究，[[澳大利亞|澳大利亞]]和[[紐西蘭|紐西蘭]]的研究人員報告，睡眠不足所產生的某些危險影響，與[[酒後駕駛|酒後駕駛]]相同。<ref name="Drunkhazard">{{cite journal |vauthors=Williamson AM, Feyer AM |title=Moderate sleep deprivation produces impairments in cognitive and motor performance equivalent to legally prescribed levels of alcohol intoxication |journal=Occup. Environ. Med. |volume=57 |issue=10 |pages=649–55 |year=2000 |pmid=10984335 |pmc=1739867 |doi= 10.1136/oem.57.10.649}}</ref>持續駕車17-19小時的人比[[血液酒精濃度|血液酒精濃度]]為0.05%（這是大多數[[西歐|西歐]]國家和澳大利亞對酒駕的法定限制）的人表現更差。另一項研究顯示，持續駕車16小時後，駕駛者的性能開始下降，而到21小時的時候，嚴重程度相當於血液酒精濃度為0.08%，這已達到[[加拿大|加拿大]]、美國、和[[英國|英國]]酒後駕駛的血液酒精濃度限制。<ref name="FatigueandAlcohol">{{cite journal |author1=Dawson, Drew  |author2=Kathryn Reid |title=Fatigue, alcohol and performance impairment |journal=Nature |volume=388 |issue=6639 |year=1997 |page=235 |doi=10.1038/40775 |pmid=9230429|bibcode=1997Natur.388..235D |s2cid=4424846 |doi-access=free }}</ref>
 
貨車和客車司機的疲勞問題已引起許多國家當局的關注，這些國家也制定專門法律，以降低因司機疲勞而發生交通事故的風險。不同國家和地區使用的駕駛法規中都有關於最短休息時間、最長排班時間長度、和班次間最短間隔時間的規定，例如[[歐洲聯盟|歐洲聯盟]]的{{le|司機工作時間規定|Drivers' working hours}}，和美國的{{le|駕駛服務時間|hours of service}}規定。
 
發生在1989年的[[阿拉斯加港灣漏油事件|阿拉斯加港灣漏油事件]]是美國史上第二大漏油事件。這起事故發生在[[埃克森美孚|埃克森美孚]]的一艘油輪在[[阿拉斯加州|阿拉斯加州]][[威廉王子灣|威廉王子灣]]撞上礁石後。大約有1,080萬[[加侖|加侖]]的[[原油|原油]]洩漏到海上。這起事故造成巨大的環境破壞，包括數十萬隻鳥類和海洋生物的死亡。造成事故的近因是船長以及整體船員都感到疲勞和睡眠不足。<ref name="AUTOREF5">{{cite web|url=http://www.gregpalast.com/court-rewards-exxon-for-valdez-oil-spill/|title=Court Rewards Exxon for Valdez Oil Spill – Greg Palast|first=Greg|last=Palast|date=2008-06-25|access-date=2021-11-01|archive-date=2021-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211029184821/https://www.gregpalast.com/court-rewards-exxon-for-valdez-oil-spill/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{ProQuest|2092623770}}</ref>
 
===睡眠轉換===
睡眠傾向(Sleep propensity，SP)可定義為從清醒狀態轉換到入睡狀態的就緒程度，或者如果已經入睡，則維持睡眠狀態的能力。<ref>Schulz, H., Bes, E., Jobert, M. (1997). Modelling Sleep Propensity and Sleep Disturbances. In: Meier-Ewert K., Okawa M. (eds) Sleep—Wake Disorders. Springer. doi:[https://doi.org/10.1007/978-1-4899-0245-0_2 10.1007/978-1-4899-0245-0_2]</ref>睡眠剝奪會導致睡眠潛伏期（入睡所需的時間）減少，而讓這種傾向增加，可透過[[多項生理睡眠檢查|多項生理睡眠檢查]](PSG)來衡量。<ref name="Durmer2005">{{cite journal |vauthors= Durmer JS, Dinges DF | year = 2005 | title = Neurocognitive Consequences of Sleep Deprivation | journal = Semin Neurol | volume = 25 | issue = 1| pages = 117–129 | doi = 10.1055/s-2005-867080 | pmid = 15798944 | pmc = 3564638 }}</ref>睡眠傾向也可在從非快速動眼睡眠的輕度階段到更深的[[慢波睡眠|慢波睡眠]]的過程中，被縮短的轉換期作為指標來衡量。<ref name="Durmer2005" />
平均而言，一夜無眠後，健康成年人的睡眠潛伏期會縮短幾分鐘，而從非快速動眼睡眠的輕度階段到到慢波睡眠的潛伏期則會減半。<ref name="Durmer2005" />睡眠潛伏期通常使用多次入睡潛伏期間測試(multiple sleep latency test，MSLT)進行測量。相比之下，維持覺醒測試 (maintenance of wakefulness test，MWT)也使用到睡眠潛伏期，但種測試是衡量參與者保持清醒（當被要求時），而不是入睡的能力。<ref name="Durmer2005" />
 
===睡眠 - 喚醒週期===
對睡眠剝奪的研究，顯示它對情緒、認知、和運動功能的影響，會由於睡眠 - 覺醒週期的失調和睡眠傾向而增加。<ref name="Durmer2005" />多項研究確定丘腦和控制晝夜節律和[[體內平衡|體內平衡]]的多個神經系統的作用，對於了解睡眠剝奪會有幫助。<ref name="Durmer2005" /><ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Saper CB, Chou TC, Scammell TE | year = 2001 | title = The sleep switch: hypothalamic control of sleep and wakefulness | journal = Trends Neurosci | volume = 24 | issue = 12| pages = 726–731 | doi = 10.1016/S0166-2236(00)02002-6 | pmid = 11718878 | s2cid = 206027570 }}</ref>為描述睡眠 - 覺醒週期的時間過程，可引用調節睡眠的兩過程模型。<ref name="Durmer2005" />
 
這個模型提出體內平衡過程（過程S）和一個晝夜節律過程（過程C），它們相互作用決定睡眠的時間和強度。<ref name="Borbély2016">{{cite journal |vauthors= Borbély AA, Daan S, Wirz-Justice A | year = 2016 | title = The two‐process model of sleep regulation: a reappraisal | journal = J Sleep Res. | volume = 25 | issue = 2| pages = 131–143 | doi = 10.1111/jsr.12371 | pmid = 26762182 | doi-access = free }}</ref>過程S代表驅動睡眠的作用，在清醒期間增加，在睡眠期間減少，直到某種閾值水準，而過程C是負責這些水準的振盪器。當睡眠被剝奪時，體內平衡壓力會累積到即使在最高的晝夜節律驅動之下，清醒功能也會降低的程度。<ref name="Durmer2005" /><ref name="Borbély2016" />
 
===微睡眠===
當一個人嚴重睡眠不足時，微睡眠就會出現。微睡眠通常持續幾秒鐘，當個人在感到困倦而試圖保持清醒時最常發生。<ref name="#1">{{Cite web|url = http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu/need-sleep/glossary/k-m|title = Glossary K-M|date = 2012|website = Get Sleep|publisher = Harvard Medical School|url-status = live|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402122751/http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu/need-sleep/glossary/k-m|archive-date = 2015-04-02}}</ref>而個人通常在做些單調的事情時（譬如開車、看書、或盯著電腦）會陷入微睡眠狀態。<ref name="#1"/>微睡眠類似於{{le|短暫性意識喪失|Blackout (drug-related amnesia)}}，有這樣狀況的人不會注意到這類事正在發生。
 
有種甚至更輕的睡眠在長時間被維持不睡的大鼠身上發現。這種被稱為{{le|局部睡眠|local sleep}}的過程，特定的局部大腦區域會進入短暫（約80毫秒）但頻繁（約40次/分鐘），宛如NREM狀態的時期。雖然大鼠神經元在此間斷發生的時期是在關閉狀態，而看來似乎清醒，卻在測試中表現不佳。<ref>{{cite journal | title=Local sleep in awake rats|vauthors=Vyazovskiy VV, Olcese U, Hanlon EC, Nir Y, Cirelli C, Tononi G | journal=Nature| year=2011| volume=472| pages=443–447 |lay-url= |doi=10.1038/nature10009 | issue=7344 | pmid=21525926 | pmc=3085007 | bibcode=2011Natur.472..443V }}</ref>
 
===心血管疾病===
睡眠時間減少與許多心血管不良後果有關聯。<ref>{{Cite web|date=2019-02-13|title=CDC - Sleep and Chronic Disease - Sleep and Sleep Disorders|url=https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/about_sleep/chronic_disease.html|access-date=2021-01-21|website=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|archive-date=2021-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211220064714/https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/about_sleep/chronic_disease.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Knutson|first1=Kristen L.|last2=Van Cauter|first2=Eve|last3=Rathouz|first3=Paul J.|last4=Yan|first4=Lijing L.|last5=Hulley|first5=Stephen B.|last6=Liu|first6=Kiang|last7=Lauderdale|first7=Diane S.|date=2009-06-08|title=Association between sleep and blood pressure in midlife: the CARDIA sleep study|journal=Archives of Internal Medicine|volume=169|issue=11|pages=1055–1061|doi=10.1001/archinternmed.2009.119|issn=1538-3679|pmc=2944774|pmid=19506175}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=King|first1=Christopher Ryan|last2=Knutson|first2=Kristen L.|last3=Rathouz|first3=Paul J.|last4=Sidney|first4=Steve|last5=Liu|first5=Kiang|last6=Lauderdale|first6=Diane S.|date=2008-12-24|title=Short sleep duration and incident coronary artery calcification|journal=JAMA|volume=300|issue=24|pages=2859–2866|doi=10.1001/jama.2008.867|issn=1538-3598|pmc=2661105|pmid=19109114}}</ref>[[美國心臟協會|美國心臟協會]]表示，睡眠不足是導致不良心臟代謝症狀和結果的危險因素。協會隨著其他已知的相關因素（如[[血壓|血壓]]、[[膽固醇|膽固醇]]、飲食、葡萄糖、體重、[[吸菸|吸菸]]、和運動）之外，也推薦養成健康的睡眠習慣，以維持心臟的健康。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=St-Onge|first1=Marie-Pierre|last2=Grandner|first2=Michael A.|last3=Brown|first3=Devin|last4=Conroy|first4=Molly B.|last5=Jean-Louis|first5=Girardin|last6=Coons|first6=Michael|last7=Bhatt|first7=Deepak L.|date=2016-11-01|title=Sleep Duration and Quality: Impact on Lifestyle Behaviors and Cardiometabolic Health: A Scientific Statement From the American Heart Association|journal=Circulation|volume=134|issue=18|pages=e367–e386|doi=10.1161/CIR.0000000000000444|issn=1524-4539|pmc=5567876|pmid=27647451}}</ref>[[美國疾病控制與預防中心|美國疾病控制與預防中心]]（CDC）指出，每天睡眠少於7小時的成年人與睡眠充足的相比，更容易患慢性健康問題，包括心心臟病、[[冠狀動脈疾病|冠狀動脈疾病]]、和[[中風|中風]]。<ref>{{Cite web|date=2019-03-05|title=CDC - Data and Statistics - Sleep and Sleep Disorders|url=https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/data_statistics.html|access-date=2021-01-21|website=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|archive-date=2022-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220116050336/https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/data_statistics.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
在一項針對160,000多名健康、非肥胖成年人做跟踪研究，自我報告每天睡眠時間少於6小時的受試者在發生多項心臟代謝危險因素的風險會增加。他們呈現的是[[代謝症候群|代謝症候群]] - [[腹部肥胖|腹部肥胖]]增加、空腹[[血糖|血糖]]升高、[[高血壓|高血壓]]、[[低高密度脂蛋白|低高密度脂蛋白]]升高、{{le|高三酸甘油脂血症|hypertriglyceridemia}}。在這項研究中，由睡眠時間長短所產生的作用並未受到有無失眠的影響。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Deng|first1=Han-Bing|last2=Tam|first2=Tony|last3=Zee|first3=Benny Chung-Ying|last4=Chung|first4=Roger Yat-Nork|last5=Su|first5=Xuefen|last6=Jin|first6=Lei|last7=Chan|first7=Ta-Chien|last8=Chang|first8=Ly-Yun|last9=Yeoh|first9=Eng-Kiong|last10=Lao|first10=Xiang Qian|date=2017-10-01|title=Short Sleep Duration Increases Metabolic Impact in Healthy Adults: A Population-Based Cohort Study|journal=Sleep|volume=40|issue=10|doi=10.1093/sleep/zsx130|issn=1550-9109|pmid=28977563|doi-access=free}}</ref>
 
[[英國生物樣品庫|英國生物樣品庫]]對近500,000名沒有心血管疾病的成年人做研究，在7年的隨訪期間中，發現每天睡眠時間少於6小時的受試者罹患[[心肌梗死|心肌梗塞]](MI)的風險增加20%。有趣的是，當每晚超過9小時的睡眠時，也是一個危險因素。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Daghlas|first1=Iyas|last2=Dashti|first2=Hassan S.|last3=Lane|first3=Jacqueline|last4=Aragam|first4=Krishna G.|last5=Rutter|first5=Martin K.|last6=Saxena|first6=Richa|last7=Vetter|first7=Céline|date=2019-09-10|title=Sleep Duration and Myocardial Infarction|journal=Journal of the American College of Cardiology|volume=74|issue=10|pages=1304–1314|doi=10.1016/j.jacc.2019.07.022|issn=1558-3597|pmc=6785011|pmid=31488267}}</ref>
 
===免疫抑制===
由於睡眠不足可能導致的無數健康後果中，[[免疫|免疫]]系統受到破壞（[[免疫抑制|免疫抑制]]）是其中之一。雖然尚未對此十分了解，但研究人員認為睡眠為免疫系統提供足夠的能量，並讓在睡眠期間發生[[炎症|炎症]]甚為重要<ref>{{cite web
 | url = https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/how-sleep-affects-immunity
 | title = How Sleep Affects Immunity
 | publisher = Sleep Foundation
 | quote = Experts aren’t certain why this process takes place during sleep, but it is believed that several factors may be involved…..The inflammation that happens during sleep could harm physical and mental performance if it occurred during waking hours, so the body has evolved so that these processes unfold during nightly sleep.
 | date = 
 | accessdate = 2021-10-05
 | archive-date = 2022-01-05
 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220105114305/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/how-sleep-affects-immunity
 | dead-url = no
 }}</ref>
。此外，正如睡眠可增強人腦的記憶力一樣，它可以幫助鞏固免疫系統的記憶或是增強[[後天免疫系統|後天免疫系統]]。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Sleep & Immunity: Can a Lack of Sleep Make You Sick?|url=https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/how-sleep-affects-immunity|access-date=2021-01-21|website=Sleep Foundation|language=en|archive-date=2022-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220105114305/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/how-sleep-affects-immunity|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Irwin|first=Michael R.|date=November 2019|title=Sleep and inflammation: partners in sickness and in health|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31289370/|journal=Nature Reviews. Immunology|volume=19|issue=11|pages=702–715|doi=10.1038/s41577-019-0190-z|issn=1474-1741|pmid=31289370|s2cid=195847558|access-date=2021-11-01|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211050428/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31289370/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
充足的睡眠可提高利用[[疫苗|疫苗]]產生後天免疫的效果。當身體接觸疫苗中減弱或失活的[[抗原|抗原]]時，會啟動免疫反應。免疫系統學會識別抗原，並在將來再次接觸時，會開始展開攻擊。研究發現，接種疫苗後晚上不睡覺的人，不太可能產生適當的免疫反應，有時甚至需要第二劑來補強。通常睡眠不足的人也不能為身體提供足夠的時間來形成足夠的免疫記憶，而可能無法從疫苗接種中受益。<ref name=":1" />
 
每晚睡眠時間少於6小時的人較易受到[[感染|感染]]，也更容易罹患感冒或是[[流行性感冒|流行性感冒]]。睡眠不足也會把患者待在[[加護病房|加護病房]]的時間延長。<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Prather|first1=Aric A.|last2=Janicki-Deverts|first2=Denise|last3=Hall|first3=Martica H.|last4=Cohen|first4=Sheldon|date=2015-09-01|title=Behaviorally Assessed Sleep and Susceptibility to the Common Cold|journal=Sleep|volume=38|issue=9|pages=1353–1359|doi=10.5665/sleep.4968|issn=1550-9109|pmc=4531403|pmid=26118561}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Pisani|first1=Margaret A.|last2=Friese|first2=Randall S.|last3=Gehlbach|first3=Brian K.|last4=Schwab|first4=Richard J.|last5=Weinhouse|first5=Gerald L.|last6=Jones|first6=Shirley F.|date=2015-04-01|title=Sleep in the intensive care unit|journal=American Journal of Respiratory and Critical Care Medicine|volume=191|issue=7|pages=731–738|doi=10.1164/rccm.201411-2099CI|issn=1535-4970|pmc=5447310|pmid=25594808}}</ref>
 
===增加體重===
睡眠不足會導致幾種對體重增加甚為重要的激素分泌失衡。睡眠剝奪會增加[[飢餓素|飢餓素]]的水準，並降低[[瘦蛋白|瘦蛋白]]的水準，導致飢餓感增加，和對高熱量食物的渴望。<ref name="VanCauter">{{cite journal|vauthors=Van Cauter E, Spiegel K |year=1999|title=Sleep as a mediator of the relationship between socioeconomic status and health: a hypothesis|journal=Ann. N. Y. Acad. Sci.|volume=896|issue=1|pages=254–61|bibcode=1999NYASA.896..254V|doi=10.1111/j.1749-6632.1999.tb08120.x|pmid=10681902|s2cid=36513336}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Taheri|first1=Shahrad|last2=Lin|first2=Ling|last3=Austin|first3=Diane|last4=Young|first4=Terry|last5=Mignot|first5=Emmanuel|year=2004|title=Short Sleep Duration Is Associated with Reduced Leptin, Elevated Ghrelin, and Increased Body Mass Index|journal=PLOS Medicine|volume=1|issue=3|pages=e62|doi=10.1371/journal.pmed.0010062|pmc=535701|pmid=15602591}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|vauthors=Taheri S, Lin L, Austin D, Young T, Mignot E|date=December 2004|title=Short Sleep Duration Is Associated with Reduced Leptin, Elevated Ghrelin, and Increased Body Mass Index|journal=PLOS Med.|volume=1|issue=3|page=e62|doi=10.1371/journal.pmed.0010062|pmc=535701|pmid=15602591}}</ref>睡眠不足還與[[生長激素|生長激素]]減少和[[皮質醇|皮質醇]]水準升高有關聯，這與導致[[肥胖症|肥胖症]]有關。睡眠不足的人也會在白天感到困倦和疲勞，而減少運動量。肥胖症也會導致睡眠品質不佳。超重或癡肥的人可能會出現阻塞型睡眠呼吸中止症狀、[[胃食道逆流|胃食道逆流]] (GERD)、抑鬱症、[[哮喘|哮喘]]、和[[骨關節炎|骨關節炎]]，這些反過來都會把一晚好眠給擾亂。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Link Between Obesity and Sleep Deprivation|url=https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/obesity-and-sleep|access-date=2021-01-21|website=Sleep Foundation|language=en|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211050428/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/obesity-and-sleep|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
對於大鼠, 經過長時間完全剝奪睡眠，會增加食物攝入量和能量的消耗, 淨影響是體重降低，最終死亡。<ref>{{cite journal|vauthors=Everson CA, Bergmann BM, Rechtschaffen A |date=February 1989|title=Sleep deprivation in the rat: III. Total sleep deprivation|journal=Sleep|volume=12|issue=1|pages=13–21|doi=10.1093/sleep/12.1.13|pmid=2928622|doi-access=free}}</ref>這項研究得到的假設是中度慢性{{le|睡眠債務|sleep debt}}累積，伴隨習慣性過短睡眠，食慾和能量消耗會同時增加，但程式會傾向食物攝入較能量消耗為大，因為在當前的社會中隨時可取得高熱量的食物。<ref name="RatExperiments">{{cite journal|vauthors=Taheri S, Lin L, Austin D, Young T, Mignot E|date=December 2004|title=Short Sleep Duration Is Associated with Reduced Leptin, Elevated Ghrelin, and Increased Body Mass Index|journal=PLOS Med.|volume=1|issue=3|pages=e62|doi=10.1371/journal.pmed.0010062|pmc=535701|pmid=15602591}}</ref>
 
===2型糖尿病===
有人認為經歷短期睡眠限制的人比睡滿8小時的人處理葡萄糖的速度為慢，而增加罹患[[2型糖尿病|2型糖尿病]]的可能性。<ref>{{Cite web|date=2007|title=Sleep and Disease Risk|url=http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu/healthy/matters/consequences/sleep-and-disease-risk|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325003506/http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu/healthy/matters/consequences/sleep-and-disease-risk|archive-date=2016-03-25|website=Healthy Sleep|publisher=Harvard Medical School}}</ref>睡眠品質差與糖尿病，以及糖尿病前期患者的高血糖有關，但對其因果關係尚不清楚。研究人員懷疑睡眠不足會影響[[胰島素|胰島素]]、皮質醇、和[[氧化應激|氧化應激]]的分泌，繼而影響到血糖的水準。睡眠剝奪會增加飢餓素以及降低瘦蛋白的水準。睡眠不足的人較會渴望食物以彌補能量不足。這種習慣會讓血糖升高，讓他們面臨肥胖症和糖尿病的風險。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Diabetes and Sleep: Sleep Disturbances & Coping|url=https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/lack-of-sleep-and-diabetes|access-date=2021-01-21|website=Sleep Foundation|language=en|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211043107/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/physical-health/lack-of-sleep-and-diabetes|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
在2005年，一項針對1,400多名參與者的研究顯示，習慣性只睡少數幾小時的人較有可能與2型糖尿病有關聯。<ref name="DGottlieb">{{cite journal|vauthors=Gottlieb DJ, Punjabi NM, Newman AB|last4=Resnick|first4=HE|last5=Redline|first5=S|last6=Baldwin|first6=CM|last7=Nieto|first7=FJ|date=April 2005|title=Association of sleep time with diabetes mellitus and impaired glucose tolerance|journal=Arch. Intern. Med.|volume=165|issue=8|pages=863–7|doi=10.1001/archinte.165.8.863|pmid=15851636|doi-access=free}}</ref>然而由於這項研究僅著重在相關性，因此睡眠不足與糖尿病之間的因果關係尚不確定。研究報告的作者們指出一項較早的研究顯示，實驗性，而非習慣性的睡眠限制會導致葡萄糖耐力受損 (請參考{{le|糖尿病前期|Prediabetes}}中英文部分#Impaired glucose tolerance)。<ref>{{cite journal|last=Spiegel|first=K.|author2=R. Leproult|author3=E. Van Cauter|date=1999-10-23|title=Impact of sleep debt on metabolic and endocrine function|journal=The Lancet|volume=354|issue=9188|pages=1435–9|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(99)01376-8|pmid=10543671|s2cid=3854642}}</ref>
 
===其他影響===
國家睡眠基金會確定有幾個警告信號可顯示駕駛員已疲勞到危險的程度：包括搖下車窗、把收音機音量調高、難以睜開眼睛、頻頻點頭、偏離車道、和做[[白日夢|白日夢]]。對在午夜開始至早上6:00之間單獨一人駕駛的司機的風險最大。<ref name="SleepFoundationDrowsyDriving">{{cite web|date=2009-12-02|title=Drowsy Driving:Key Messages and Talking Points|url=http://www.sleepfoundation.org/sites/default/files/Drowsy%20Driving-Key%20Messages%20and%20Talking%20Points.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131126062848/http://www.sleepfoundation.org/sites/default/files/Drowsy%20Driving-Key%20Messages%20and%20Talking%20Points.pdf|archive-date=2013-11-26|work=National Sleep Foundation}}</ref>
 
睡眠不足會對個人整體表現產生負面影響，並造成重大致命事故。主要案例是在2009年2月[[科爾根航空3407號班機空難|科爾根航空3407號班機空難]]事件，造成50人死亡，部分原因是飛行員疲勞，這事件促使[[美國聯邦航空局|美國聯邦航空局]]審查航空公司的作業流程以確保飛行員得到充分休息。在2010年，有10起[[航空管制員|航空管制員]]在值班時睡著的事件，而引起管理當局的審查。由於管制員常見的輪班做法會導致他們睡眠不足，而成為發生空中交通管制事故的因素。美國聯邦航空局審查換班的做法，發現管制員並未得到很好的休息。<ref name="PlaneCrash">{{cite web|date=2010-09-10|title=Fact Sheet – Pilot Fatigue|url=http://www.faa.gov/news/fact_sheets/news_story.cfm?newsId=11857|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005194346/http://www.faa.gov/news/fact_sheets/news_story.cfm?newsId=11857|archive-date=2016-10-05|work=Federal Aviation Administration}}</ref>在2004年所做的一項研究還發現，每晚睡眠時間少於4小時的住院醫師與每晚睡眠時間超過7小時的（只佔接受調查醫師的11%）比較，犯下的錯誤超過兩倍。<ref name="MedicalErrors">{{cite journal|author1=Baldwinn, DeWitt C. Jr.|author2=Steven R. Daugherty|year=2004|title=Sleep Deprivation and Fatigue in Residency Training: Results of a National Survey of First- and Second-Year Residents|journal=Sleep|volume=27|issue=2|pages=217–223|doi=10.1093/sleep/27.2.217|pmid=15124713|doi-access=free}}</ref>
 
受調查者在經過24小時的連續睡眠剝奪後，碰到與數字有關的任務，會選擇難度較小的，但在主觀報告上，他們不會減少對任務的努力程度。自然發生的睡眠不足會影響到日常任務的選擇，而通常會選擇較不費力的。睡眠時間較短的[[青少年|青少年]]對參與需要用到精細運動協調，以及要注重細節的體育活動的意願會降低。<ref>{{cite journal|last=Engle-Friedman|first=Mindy|author2=Suzanne Riela|author3=Rama Golan|author4=Ana M. Ventuneac2|author5=Christine M. Davis1|author6=Angela D. Jefferson|author7=Donna Major|date=June 2003|title=The effect of sleep loss on next day effort|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/c45fe4c4bfc02744eb9bad28ba523d89ae9e85cb|journal=Journal of Sleep Research|volume=12|issue=2|pages=113–124|doi=10.1046/j.1365-2869.2003.00351.x|pmid=12753348|s2cid=13519528}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Engle Friedman|first1=Mindy|last2=Palencar|first2=V|last3=Riela|first3=S|year=2010|title=Sleep and effort in adolescent athletes|journal=J. Child Health Care|volume=14|issue=2|pages=131–41|doi=10.1177/1367493510362129|pmid=20435615|s2cid=7680316}}</ref>
 
嚴重的睡眠剝奪的結果與[[精神症|精神症]]類似：認知發生扭曲，會導致不適當的情緒和行為反應。<ref name="Coren">{{cite journal|last=Coren|first=Stanley|date=1998-03-01|title=Sleep Deprivation, Psychosis and Mental Efficiency|url=http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/display/article/10168/54471|url-status=live|journal=Psychiatric Times|volume=15|issue=3|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090904142025/http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/display/article/10168/54471|archive-date=2009-09-04|access-date=2009-11-25}}</ref>
 
[[宇航員|太空人]]報告說，在漫長的工作時間和保持清醒期間，以及由於晝夜節律中斷和環境因素導致的睡眠不足，會發生操作錯誤和認知能力下降（請參考{{le|太空旅行的睡眠|Sleep in space}}）。<ref>{{cite web|last=Whitmire|first=A.M.|author2=Leveton, L.B|author3=Barger, L.|author4=Brainard, G.|author5=Dinges, D.F.|author6=Klerman, E.|author7=Shea, C.|title=Risk of Performance Errors due to Sleep Loss, Circadian Desynchronization, Fatigue, and Work Overload|url=http://humanresearchroadmap.nasa.gov/evidence/reports/Sleep.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215234226/http://humanresearchroadmap.nasa.gov/evidence/reports/Sleep.pdf|archive-date=2012-02-15|access-date=2012-06-25|work=Human Health and Performance Risks of Space Exploration Missions: Evidence reviewed by the NASA Human Research Program}}</ref>
 
一項研究發現，整晚的睡眠被剝奪後，會導致第二天的[[心跳過速|心跳過速]]。<ref name="sleeptachy">{{cite journal|vauthors=Rangaraj VR, Knutson KL|date=February 2016|title=Association between sleep deficiency and cardiometabolic disease: implications for health disparities|journal=Sleep Med|volume=18|pages=19–35|doi=10.1016/j.sleep.2015.02.535|pmc=4758899|pmid=26431758}}</ref>
 
