==評估==
睡眠不足的患者會抱怨睡眠不足的症狀和體徵，例如疲勞、[[昏睡|昏睡]]、昏昏欲睡時駕車、和認知困難。除非臨床醫生特別詢問患者，否則睡眠不足很容易被忽視和未受診斷。<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=UpToDate|url=https://www.uptodate.com/contents/insufficient-sleep-evaluation-and-management?search=sleep%20deprivat&topicRef=7715&source=see_link|access-date=2021-01-28|website=www.uptodate.com|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028041832/https://www.uptodate.com/contents/insufficient-sleep-evaluation-and-management?search=sleep%20deprivat&topicRef=7715&source=see_link|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
有幾個問題對於評估睡眠時間、品質、還有睡眠受剝奪的原因很重要。睡眠模式（在平日和週末的典型就寢時間或是起床時間）、輪班工作、和小睡頻率可顯示睡眠不佳的直接原因，應討論睡眠的品質，並把疾病（如阻塞性睡眠呼吸呼吸中止和[[不寧腿綜合症|不寧腿綜合症]]）造成的原因排除<ref name=":2" />
 
利用[[睡眠日記|睡眠日記]]可得到有關睡眠模式的詳細信息。這種方式價格低廉、易於獲得、且易於使用。日記像24小時日誌般簡單，把睡眠時間，及其他相關信息做詳細記錄。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Carney|first1=Colleen E.|last2=Buysse|first2=Daniel J.|last3=Ancoli-Israel|first3=Sonia|last4=Edinger|first4=Jack D.|last5=Krystal|first5=Andrew D.|last6=Lichstein|first6=Kenneth L.|last7=Morin|first7=Charles M.|date=2012-02-01|title=The consensus sleep diary: standardizing prospective sleep self-monitoring|journal=Sleep|volume=35|issue=2|pages=287–302|doi=10.5665/sleep.1642|issn=1550-9109|pmc=3250369|pmid=22294820}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Sleep Deprivation: Causes, Symptoms, & Treatment|url=https://www.sleepfoundation.org/sleep-deprivation|access-date=2021-01-21|website=Sleep Foundation|language=en|archive-date=2022-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220111090217/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/sleep-deprivation|dead-url=no}}</ref>如果對患者的依從性有任何顧慮，可使用如睡眠時間問卷(Sleep Timing Questionnaire，STQ)等方式取代睡眠日記。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Monk|first1=Timothy H.|last2=Buysse|first2=Daniel J.|last3=Kennedy|first3=Kathy S.|last4=Pods|first4=Jaime M.|last5=DeGrazia|first5=Jean M.|last6=Miewald|first6=Jean M.|date=2003-03-15|title=Measuring sleep habits without using a diary: the sleep timing questionnaire|journal=Sleep|volume=26|issue=2|pages=208–212|doi=10.1093/sleep/26.2.208|issn=0161-8105|pmid=12683481|doi-access=free}}</ref>
 
如果對於自我報告的睡眠日記或問卷的正確性感覺有問題，掛在腕上做記錄的{{le|腕動計|Actigraphy}}也是種有用、客觀的工具。腕動計的工作原理是記錄運動，使用計算機演算法來估計總睡眠時間、入睡潛伏期、入睡後醒來時間、以及睡眠效率。有些裝置上裝有光傳感器來記錄曝光的情況。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Actigraphy|url=https://stanfordhealthcare.org/medical-tests/s/sleep-disorder-tests/procedures/actigraphy.html|access-date=2021-01-21|website=stanfordhealthcare.org|language=en|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211054504/https://stanfordhealthcare.org/medical-tests/s/sleep-disorder-tests/procedures/actigraphy.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Morgenthaler|first1=Timothy|last2=Alessi|first2=Cathy|last3=Friedman|first3=Leah|last4=Owens|first4=Judith|last5=Kapur|first5=Vishesh|last6=Boehlecke|first6=Brian|last7=Brown|first7=Terry|last8=Chesson|first8=Andrew|last9=Coleman|first9=Jack|last10=Lee-Chiong|first10=Teofilo|last11=Pancer|first11=Jeffrey|date=April 2007|title=Practice parameters for the use of actigraphy in the assessment of sleep and sleep disorders: an update for 2007|journal=Sleep|volume=30|issue=4|pages=519–529|doi=10.1093/sleep/30.4.519|issn=0161-8105|pmid=17520797|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Smith|first1=Michael T.|last2=McCrae|first2=Christina S.|last3=Cheung|first3=Joseph|last4=Martin|first4=Jennifer L.|last5=Harrod|first5=Christopher G.|last6=Heald|first6=Jonathan L.|last7=Carden|first7=Kelly A.|date=2018-07-15|title=Use of Actigraphy for the Evaluation of Sleep Disorders and Circadian Rhythm Sleep-Wake Disorders: An American Academy of Sleep Medicine Clinical Practice Guideline|journal=Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine|volume=14|issue=7|pages=1231–1237|doi=10.5664/jcsm.7230|issn=1550-9397|pmc=6040807|pmid=29991437}}</ref>
 
==管理==
雖然導致睡眠不足的原因很多，但如CDC、[[國家衛生院_(美國)|國家衛生院]]
、{{le|國家老化研究所|National Institute of Aging}}、和{{le|美國家庭醫師學會|American Academy of Family Physicians}}等組織所建議，有些基本措施可促進優質的睡眠。關鍵就是要養成良好的睡眠習慣，也稱為{{le|睡眠衛生|sleep hygiene}}。<ref>{{Cite web|title=How to Sleep Better|url=https://www.sleepfoundation.org/sleep-hygiene/healthy-sleep-tips|access-date=2021-01-14|website=Sleep Foundation|language=en|archive-date=2022-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220110045616/https://www.sleepfoundation.org/sleep-hygiene/healthy-sleep-tips|dead-url=no}}</ref>關於睡眠衛生的建議中，包括有設定固定的睡眠時間、謹慎進行小睡、保持良好的睡眠環境（溫度涼爽、少受光線和噪音騷擾、舒適的床墊和枕頭）、每天運動、避免飲酒/[[吸菸|吸菸]]/咖啡/過於豐富的晚餐、在接近就寢時間放鬆，並避免使用電子產品或做體育活動、還有在無法睡著時就不要繼續臥床。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/about_sleep/sleep_hygiene.html|title=CDC - Sleep Hygiene Tips - Sleep and Sleep Disorders|date=2019-02-13|website=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-21|archive-date=2021-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211228170701/https://www.cdc.gov/sleep/about_sleep/sleep_hygiene.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
對於長期非自願性的睡眠剝奪，在排除身體診斷症狀（例如睡眠呼吸中止）後，失眠的認知行為療法(CBT-i)通常被推薦作為一線治療。CBT-i包含五個不同的組成部分：認知療法、刺激控制、睡眠限制、睡眠衛生、以及放鬆。這些成分被證明對成人有效，具有臨床意義的效力。由於CBT-i具有副作用最小及長期的益處，因此與（慢性）藥物治療比較，會被建議優先採用。<ref name="Trauer 191">{{Cite journal|last1=Trauer|first1=James M.|last2=Qian|first2=Mary Y.|last3=Doyle|first3=Joseph S.|last4=Rajaratnam|first4=Shantha M.W.|last5=Cunnington|first5=David|date=2015-08-04|title=Cognitive Behavioral Therapy for Chronic Insomnia: A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis|journal=Annals of Internal Medicine|volume=163|issue=3|pages=191–204|doi=10.7326/M14-2841|issn=0003-4819|pmid=26054060|s2cid=21617330}}</ref>
 
有幾種做法可幫助提高警覺性，同時抵消睡眠剝奪的影響。當碰到急性睡眠剝奪時，在短時間內通常會使用咖啡因來提高清醒度；但如果經常攝取咖啡因，效果會降低。<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.aasmnet.org/resources/factsheets/sleepdeprivation.pdf|title = Sleep Deprivation|date = 2008|access-date = 2015-03-25|website = American Academy of Sleep Medicine|url-status = live|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150226011724/http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/SleepDeprivation.pdf|archive-date = 2015-02-26}}</ref>美國睡眠醫學會推薦的其他做法包括在預期剝奪之前的預防性睡眠、小睡、使用其他[[興奮劑|興奮劑]]、或是前面幾種的組合。但對抗睡眠不足的唯一確定，以及安全的方法，是增加在夜間的睡眠時間。<ref name="SleepFactSheet">{{cite web |work=American Academy of Sleep Medicine |title=Sleep Deprivation Fact Sheet |url=http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/SleepDeprivation.pdf |date=2009-12-02 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226011724/http://www.aasmnet.org/Resources/FactSheets/SleepDeprivation.pdf |archive-date=2015-02-26  }}</ref>
 
==睡眠剝奪的用途==
===達成濫用及控制的目的===
睡眠剝奪可用於讓受到[[虐待|虐待]]者產生迷惑，而達到[[虐待關係中的權力與控制|濫用權力及控制]]的目的。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.domesticshelters.org/domestic-violence-articles-information/sleep-deprivation-as-abuse |title=Sleep Deprivation Used as Abuse Tactic |access-date=2021-11-01 |archive-date=2019-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190121232509/https://www.domesticshelters.org/domestic-violence-articles-information/sleep-deprivation-as-abuse |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://federation.edu.au/staff/working-at-feduni/feduni-against-violence/family-and-domestic-violence?a=282376 |title=Family and Domestic Violence - Healthy Work Healthy Living Tip Sheet |access-date=2021-11-01 |archive-date=2019-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190519200619/https://federation.edu.au/staff/working-at-feduni/feduni-against-violence/family-and-domestic-violence?a=282376 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
===審訊===
睡眠剝奪可當作審訊的手段，這會導致法庭對於這種方式是否被認定為[[酷刑|酷刑]]的形式。<ref>{{cite news|date=2009-10-02|title=Binyam Mohamed torture appeal lost by UK government...|work=BBC News|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/8507852.stm|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100211025746/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/8507852.stm|archive-date=2010-02-11}}</ref>
 
有種審訊技術，讓受審訊的對象維持在不睡覺的狀況態幾天，當最終對象入睡時，立即將其喚醒，然後繼續詢問。在1977年至1983年擔任[[以色列|以色列]]總理的{{le|梅納罕·比金|Menachem Begin}}描述他被[[蘇聯|蘇聯]][[內務人民委員部|內務人民委員部]]（NKVD）監禁，並被剝奪睡眠的情況：
 
{{Quote|被審訊的囚犯的腦筋開始變得模糊。精神疲憊不堪，腿部無力，當時只有個願望：就是“睡覺”……任何有這種經驗的人都知道，即​​使是飢餓和口渴都無法與之相比。<ref>{{cite book |author=Begin, Menachem |title=White nights: the story of a prisoner in Russia |publisher=Harper & Row |location=San Francisco |year=1979 |isbn=978-0-06-010289-0 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/whitenightsstory00begi }}</ref>}}
睡眠剝奪是1970年代英國政府採用的{{le|詢問五法|five techniques}}中的一種。[[歐洲人權法院|歐洲人權法院]]裁定，這五種方法“沒造成所謂酷刑所隱含的特別強烈和殘忍的折磨...... [但]相等於{{le|不人道或有辱人格做法|Inhuman or degrading treatment }}”，違反[[歐洲人權公約|歐洲人權公約]]的精神。<ref name="Ireland v. UK-102">[http://cmiskp.echr.coe.int/tkp197/view.asp?action=html&documentId=695383&portal=hbkm&source=externalbydocnumber&table=F69A27FD8FB86142BF01C1166DEA398649 Ireland v. the United Kingdom] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514052109/http://cmiskp.echr.coe.int/tkp197/view.asp?action=html&documentId=695383&portal=hbkm&source=externalbydocnumber&table=F69A27FD8FB86142BF01C1166DEA398649|date=14 May 2011}} paragraph 102</ref>
 
[[美國司法部|美國司法部]]於2002年8月發布四份備忘錄，描述[[中央情報局|中央情報局]]（CIA）所使用的審訊技術。第一份備忘錄描述對{{le|阿布·祖拜達|Abu Zubaydah}}（被當作恐怖分子的後勤專家）的審訊所使用的10種技術，包括剝奪睡眠。由{{le|史提芬·布萊德布雷|Steven G. Bradbury}}於2005年5月簽署的幾份備忘錄聲稱，把一名穿著尿布的囚犯銬在天花板上，透過強迫式睡眠剝奪長達180小時（7+1⁄2 天）<ref name="latimes2009-04-17">{{cite news|last1=Miller|first=Greg|last2=Meyer|first2=Josh|date=2009-04-17|title=Obama assures intelligence officials they won't be prosecuted over interrogations|newspaper=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|url=https://articles.latimes.com/2009/apr/17/nation/na-interrogation17|access-date=2016-07-10|archive-date=2016-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161016204042/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/apr/17/nation/na-interrogation17|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="memo10May2005-1">{{cite web|last=Bradbury|first=Steven G.|date=2005-05-10|title=Memorandum for John Rizzo|url=http://media.luxmedia.com/aclu/olc_05102005_bradbury46pg.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106150408/http://media.luxmedia.com/aclu/olc_05102005_bradbury46pg.pdf|archive-date=2011-11-06|access-date=2011-10-24|publisher=ACLU|page=14}}</ref>並不構成酷刑，<ref name="time">{{cite news|last=Scherer|first=Michael|date=2009-04-21|title=Scientists Claim CIA Misused Work on Sleep Deprivation|newspaper=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|url=http://content.time.com/time/nation/article/0,8599,1892897,00.html|access-date=2017-02-02|archive-date=2017-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203161835/http://content.time.com/time/nation/article/0,8599,1892897,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>根據美國法律，多種審訊方法（包括剝奪睡眠）的組合也不構成酷刑。<ref name="Explaining and Authorizing Specific Interrogation Techniques">{{cite news|date=2009-04-17|title=Explaining and Authorizing Specific Interrogation Techniques|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2009/04/17/us/politics/20090417-interrogation-techniques.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019152619/http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2009/04/17/us/politics/20090417-interrogation-techniques.html|archive-date=2017-10-19}}</ref><ref name="OPR">{{cite report|url=https://www.aclu.org/files/pdfs/natsec/opr20100219/20090729_OPR_Final_Report_with_20100719_declassifications.pdf|title=Investigation into the Office of Legal Counsel's Memoranda Concerning Issues Relating to the Central Intelligence Agency's Use of "Enhanced Interrogation Techniques" on Suspected Terrorists|author=Department of Justice Office of Professional Responsibility|date=29 July 2009|publisher=[[United_States_Department_of_Justice|United States Department of Justice]]|pages=133–138|author-link=Office of Professional Responsibility|access-date=29 May 2017|archive-date=2020-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026171950/https://www.aclu.org/files/pdfs/natsec/opr20100219/20090729_OPR_Final_Report_with_20100719_declassifications.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>這些備忘錄在[[巴拉克·歐巴馬|歐巴馬]]總統執政的頭幾個月就被否定和撤回。<ref name="latimes2009-04-17" />
 
使用極端式睡眠剝奪作為酷刑的問題，在贊成和反對方面都有倡導者。2006年，[[澳大利亞律政部|澳大利亞律政部]]部長{{le|菲利普·拉多克|Philip Ruddock}}辯稱剝奪睡眠並不構成酷刑。<ref name="SleepTorture2">{{cite news|author=Hassan T|date=2006-10-03|title=Sleep deprivation remains red-hot question|work=PM|publisher=abc.net.au|url=http://www.abc.net.au/pm/content/2006/s1754821.htm|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011211903/http://abc.net.au/pm/content/2006/s1754821.htm|archive-date=2007-10-11}}</ref>{{le|國際特赦組織澳大利亞分部|Amnesty International Australia}}發言人妮可·比斯克(Nicole Bieske)曾表達組織的意見：“至少剝奪睡眠是殘忍、不人道和有辱人格的。如果長時間使用，那就是酷刑。”<ref name="SleepTorture">{{cite news|date=2006-10-03|title=Sleep deprivation is torture: Amnesty|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|agency=AAP|url=https://www.smh.com.au/news/National/Sleep-deprivation-is-torture-Amnesty/2006/10/03/1159641317450.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071027141433/http://www.smh.com.au/news/National/Sleep-deprivation-is-torture-Amnesty/2006/10/03/1159641317450.html|archive-date=2007-10-27}}</ref>
 
===治療抑鬱症===
研究顯示睡眠限制在治療抑鬱症方面有某些潛力。<ref name="Sleep and depression review"/>患有抑鬱症的人往往較早出現快速眼動睡眠，快速眼動次數增加；因此，監測患者的腦電圖，並在發生快速眼動睡眠期間把他們喚醒，似乎有{{le|治療效果|therapeutic effect|療效}}，把抑鬱症狀減輕。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Carlson|first=Neil|title=Physiology of Behavior|url=https://archive.org/details/physiologybehavi00carl_811|publisher=Pearson|year=2013|isbn=9780205239399|edition=11th|location=Boston|pages=[https://archive.org/details/physiologybehavi00carl_811/page/n598 578]–579}}</ref>這種治療被稱為{{le|喚醒療法|wake therapy}}。有多達60%的憂鬱症患者在睡眠被剝奪後會改善，但大多數會在第二天晚上再復發。這種效應被證明與[[腦源性神經營養因子|腦源性神經營養因子]](BDNF) 的增加有關。<ref>{{Cite journal|author=Gorgulu Y, Caliyurt O|last2=Caliyurt|date=Sep 2009|title=Rapid antidepressant effects of sleep deprivation therapy correlates with serum BDNF changes in major depression|journal=Brain Res. Bull.|volume=80|issue=3|pages=158–62|doi=10.1016/j.brainresbull.2009.06.016|pmid=19576267|s2cid=7672556}}</ref>在2014年對受到睡眠剝奪的人體[[代謝物組|代謝物組]]的綜合評估發現，在醒來後24小時後有27種代謝物增加，由於血清素、[[色氨酸|色氨酸]]、和[[牛磺酸|牛磺酸]]增加，表示睡眠剝奪對抗抑鬱可發揮作用。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Davies|first1=S. K.|last2=Ang|first2=J. E.|last3=Revell|first3=V. L.|last4=Holmes|first4=B|last5=Mann|first5=A|last6=Robertson|first6=F. P.|last7=Cui|first7=N|last8=Middleton|first8=B|last9=Ackermann|first9=K|last10=Kayser|first10=M|last11=Thumser|first11=A. E.|date=2014-07-22|title=Effect of sleep deprivation on the human metabolome|journal=Proc Natl Acad Sci USA|volume=111|issue=29|pages=10761–6|bibcode=2014PNAS..11110761D|doi=10.1073/pnas.1402663111|pmc=4115565|pmid=25002497|last12=Raynaud|first12=F. I.|last13=Skene|first13=D. J.|doi-access=free}}</ref>
 
利用睡眠剝奪，加上藥物醫療，或是[[光照治療|光照治療]]和相位超前（比正常時間更早就寢）相結合，可把復發率降低。<ref name="Ncbi">{{cite journal|author=Wirz-Justice A, Van den Hoofdakker RH|last2=Van Den Hoofdakker|date=August 1999|title=Sleep deprivation in depression: what do we know, where do we go?|journal=Biol. Psychiatry|volume=46|issue=4|pages=445–53|doi=10.1016/S0006-3223(99)00125-0|pmid=10459393|s2cid=15428567}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=WIRZ-JUSTICE|first1=ANNA|last2=BENEDETTI|first2=FRANCESCO|last3=BERGER|first3=MATHIAS|last4=LAM|first4=RAYMOND W.|last5=MARTINY|first5=KLAUS|last6=TERMAN|first6=MICHAEL|last7=WU|first7=JOSEPH C.|date=2005-03-10|title=Chronotherapeutics (light and wake therapy) in affective disorders|journal=Psychological Medicine|volume=35|issue=7|pages=939–944|doi=10.1017/S003329170500437X|pmid=16045060|doi-access=free}}</ref>許多[[三環類抗抑鬱藥|三環類抗抑鬱藥]]可抑制快速眼動睡眠，為情緒和睡眠之間的聯繫提供額外的證據。<ref name="SleepDepEmedicinehealth">[http://www.emedicinehealth.com/articles/42677-5.asp Disorders That Disrupt Sleep (Parasomnias)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051222202250/http://www.emedicinehealth.com/articles/42677-5.asp|date=22 December 2005}}. eMedicineHealth</ref>同樣的，[[反苯環丙胺|反苯環丙胺]]已被證明在足夠的劑量下可完全抑制快速眼動睡眠。
 
===治療失眠===
治療失眠，可採用短時間的睡眠剝奪。一些常見的睡眠剝奪已被證明對治療失眠的認知行為療法有反應。其中有個組成部分是“睡眠限制”的做法，以恢復睡眠的體內平衡，並鼓勵正常的“睡眠效率”發生。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Miller|first1=CB|display-authors=etal|date=October 2014|title=The evidence base of sleep restriction therapy for treating insomnia disorder.|journal=Sleep Medicine Reviews|volume=18|issue=5|pages=415–24|doi=10.1016/j.smrv.2014.01.006|pmid=24629826}}</ref>刺激控制和睡眠限制療法（請參考{{le|治療失眠的認知行為療法|Cognitive behavioral therapy for insomnia}}英文部分#sleep restriction therapy）的主要目標是在床和睡眠之間建立關聯。雖然在使用認知行為療法（CBT-I）時採用睡眠限制療法可顯示有療效，但單獨使用時的療效尚未得到證實。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Miller|first1=Christopher B.|last2=Espie|first2=Colin A.|last3=Epstein|first3=Dana R.|last4=Friedman|first4=Leah|last5=Morin|first5=Charles M.|last6=Pigeon|first6=Wilfred R.|last7=Spielman|first7=Arthur J.|last8=Kyle|first8=Simon D.|date=October 2014|title=The evidence base of sleep restriction therapy for treating insomnia disorder|journal=Sleep Medicine Reviews|volume=18|issue=5|pages=415–424|doi=10.1016/j.smrv.2014.01.006|pmid=24629826}}</ref><ref name="Trauer 191" />
 
==美國睡眠習慣的變化==
[[國家地理_(雜誌)|國家地理雜誌]]報導說，由於工作、社交活動、以及24小時皆可使用的家庭娛樂和互聯網，導致現代人們的睡眠比[[近世|近代早期]]少。<ref>[http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2005/02/0224_050224_sleep.html "U.S. Racking Up Huge "Sleep Debt""] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061210051110/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2005/02/0224_050224_sleep.html |date=10 December 2006 }}, ''[[National_Geographic_Magazine|National Geographic Magazine]]'', 24 February 2005</ref>《[[今日美國|今日美國]]》在2007年報導說，美國大多數成年人的平均睡眠時間比40年前的少了大約一個小時。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/health/2007-11-25-sleep-deficit_N.htm | work=USA Today | first=Kathleen | last=Fackelmann | title=Study: Sleep deficit may be impossible to make up | date=2007-11-25 | url-status=live | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120628121051/http://www.usatoday.com/news/health/2007-11-25-sleep-deficit_N.htm | archive-date=2012-06-28 }}</ref>
 
其他研究人員對此說法表示質疑。《{{le|睡眠|Sleep (journal)}}》雜誌（月刊）在2004年的一篇社論指出，根據現有數據，近幾十年來成年人在24小時內的平均睡眠時數沒有顯著改變。此外，社論表示健康成年人需要的正常睡眠時間有個範圍，而非固定時數，許多用來顯示整個人群有長期嗜睡的指標，並不能通過科學的審查。<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Horne |first=Jim |title=Is there a sleep debt? |journal=Sleep |volume=27 |issue=6 |pages=1047–9 |date=September 2004 |pmid=15532195}}</ref>
 
[[美國勞工部|美國勞工部]]所屬的{{le|美國勞工統計局|Bureau of Labor Statistics}}公佈的1965-1985年和1998-2001年美國時間使用調查數據，把兩者比較，美國成年人平均睡眠、小睡、和休息的[[中位數|中位數]]變化低於0.7%，從1965-1985年的平均每天482分鐘，到1998-2001年的479分鐘。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popcenter.umd.edu/sdaweb/glaser/Doc/GLAS.htm|title=National Time Use Studies (1965–1985)|work=umd.edu|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060907204651/http://www.popcenter.umd.edu/sdaweb/glaser/Doc/GLAS.htm|archive-date=2006-09-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popcenter.umd.edu/sdaweb/diary9801/Doc/Diar.htm|title=National Time Use Studies (1998 - 2001)|work=umd.edu|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060907204005/http://www.popcenter.umd.edu/sdaweb/diary9801/Doc/Diar.htm|archive-date=2006-09-07}}</ref>
 
==最長的不睡覺時間==
蘭迪·加德納 (Randy Gardner) 擁有科學上，人類刻意不使用任何興奮劑而故意不睡覺，保持清醒264小時（11 天）的記錄（請參考{{le|蘭迪·加德納睡眠剝奪試驗|Randy Gardner sleep deprivation experiment}}），打破檀香山的{{le|湯姆·朗茲|Tom Rounds}}在[[檀香山|檀香山]]創下的的260小時記錄。<ref name="Coren"/>

